## 1. Prerequisites

Before running any commands, make sure the following are installed on the machine:

| Tool | Version Used | How to Get It |
|------|-------------|---------------|
| **Python** | 3.10.3 (64-bit) | https://www.python.org/downloads/ |
| **XAMPP** | Any recent version | https://www.apachefriends.org/ |
| **MySQL** (via XAMPP) | MariaDB 10.x | Included with XAMPP |
| **Git** | Any | https://git-scm.com/ (optional) |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Python **must be 64-bit** (win_amd64). The prebuilt `dlib` wheel only works with 64-bit Python.
> XAMPP's MySQL service must be **started** before running the app.

---

## 2. Project Structure

```
smart_attendance/
├── app.py                     ← Main Flask application (entry point)
├── config.py                  ← Database credentials, file paths, config
├── requirements.txt           ← Python dependencies list
├── venv/                      ← Python virtual environment
├── database/
│   └── schema.sql             ← MySQL schema (run this ONCE to create tables)
├── models/
│   └── db.py                  ← Database helper (execute_query function)
├── attendance/
│   └── attendance.py          ← Attendance logic (mark, get, summarise)
├── face_recognition_module/
│   ├── capture_faces.py       ← Webcam face capture
│   ├── encode_faces.py        ← HOG face encoding
│   └── recognize_faces.py     ← Live recognition loop
├── dataset/
│   └── faces/                 ← Auto-created; stores student photo sets
├── static/
│   ├── css/style.css
│   └── js/                    ← dashboard.js, main.js, register.js, etc.
└── templates/                 ← Jinja2 HTML templates
```

