## 5. Accessing the Application

Once the server is running, open any browser and go to:

| URL | Page | Auth Required |
|-----|------|:---:|
| `http://127.0.0.1:5000` | Home / Landing page | No |
| `http://127.0.0.1:5000/login` | Admin login form | No |
| `http://127.0.0.1:5000/dashboard` | Stats dashboard + face recognition controls | Yes |
| `http://127.0.0.1:5000/register` | Register new students + capture faces | Yes |
| `http://127.0.0.1:5000/attendance-log` | View/filter attendance records | Yes |

**Access from another device on the same local network:**
```
http://<server-LAN-IP>:5000
# Example: http://192.168.10.153:5000
```
The LAN IP is displayed in the Flask startup output.

