## 7. Quick Re-setup Checklist

Copy this checklist to use on a new computer:

```
SMART ATTENDANCE SYSTEM — NEW MACHINE SETUP
============================================

PREREQUISITES
  □ Install Python 3.10 (64-bit) — python.org/downloads
  □ Install XAMPP — apachefriends.org
  □ Start MySQL from XAMPP Control Panel

PROJECT SETUP
  □ Copy / clone the project to: C:\xampp\htdocs\smart_attendance\
  □ Open PowerShell and cd into that directory

VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT
  □ python -m venv venv          (only if venv folder doesn't exist)

INSTALL PYTHON DEPENDENCIES
  □ .\venv\Scripts\pip.exe install -r requirements.txt
       If C: disk is low, add: --cache-dir "D:\pip_cache"
       and run: $env:TEMP="D:\pip_tmp"; $env:TMP="D:\pip_tmp"

INSTALL DLIB (if pip install above fails for dlib)
  □ Download pre-built wheel:
      Invoke-WebRequest `
        -Uri "https://github.com/z-mahmud22/Dlib_Windows_Python3.x/raw/refs/heads/main/dlib-19.22.99-cp310-cp310-win_amd64.whl" `
        -OutFile "D:\dlib.whl" -UseBasicParsing
  □ .\venv\Scripts\pip.exe install "D:\dlib.whl"
  □ .\venv\Scripts\pip.exe install "face-recognition>=1.3,<2.0"

DATABASE
  □ & "C:\xampp\mysql\bin\mysql.exe" -u root -e "SOURCE database/schema.sql;"
  □ Fix admin password hash (run Python script from Section 3.8)
  □ Verify: .\venv\Scripts\python.exe -c "..."  (login check prints True)

START & VERIFY
  □ .\venv\Scripts\python.exe app.py
  □ Open browser: http://127.0.0.1:5000
  □ Log in: admin / admin123
  □ Confirm dashboard, register, and attendance-log pages all load
```

